Defendant Lamont M Magee in court with attorney Anne A Devitt.  Defendant Lamont M Magee in custody.  Jesica A Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.  

Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  66 MONTHS, CONCURRENT with 11CF578 and any other sentence with credit for 91 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 30 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 36 MONTHS.
The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program after serving first 15 months of this sentence.

CONDITIONS OF SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay victim/witness surcharge, fees, assessments, surcharges,and all other mandatory costs; 
The Court ordered restitution set at $0 (zero). Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of 600.00 including all applicable mandatory surcharges including DNA, PLUS a $50.00 surcharge for the Ignition Interlock Device be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 36 months.    Court orders defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 24 months to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license.  

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

Appeal rights given.
